  "prompt": "How would you know that a guy has a crush on you or likes you even though if you are friends?",
  "response": "Noticing that a guy has a crush on you, especially when you're friends, can be tricky because he might try to hide his feelings to preserve the friendship. However, there are some subtle (and not-so-subtle) signs to look out for:\n\n### 1. **Increased Attention**\n   - He pays extra attention to you, listens intently, and remembers small details about what you say.\n   - He often makes eye contact and holds it longer than usual.\n\n### 2. **Physical Touch**\n   - He finds excuses to touch you, like playfully nudging you, touching your arm, or giving hugs.\n   - He might sit or stand closer to you than necessary.\n\n### 3. **Acts of Kindness**\n   - He goes out of his way to do things for you, like offering to help with tasks or giving you thoughtful gifts.\n   - He\u2019s extra supportive and wants to make you happy.\n\n### 4. **Jealousy or Protectiveness**\n   - He seems uncomfortable or acts differently when you talk about other guys or when someone else flirts with you.\n   - He might try to subtly insert himself into situations where he feels threatened.\n\n### 5. **Nervousness or Awkwardness**\n   - He acts more nervous or awkward around you, like stumbling over his words or fidgeting.\n   - He might seem overly self-conscious about how he looks or behaves when he\u2019s with you.\n\n### 6. **Frequent Communication**\n   - He texts or calls you often, even for no particular reason.\n   - He responds quickly to your messages and keeps the conversation going.\n\n### 7. **Teasing or Flirting**\n   - He teases you in a playful, light-hearted way, which can be a form of flirting.\n   - He compliments you more often than he does other people.\n\n### 8. **Hanging Out One-on-One**\n   - He suggests spending time alone with you, like grabbing coffee or going to events together.\n   - He seems excited about plans that involve just the two of you.\n\n### 9. **Body Language Cues**\n   - He faces you directly, leans in when you\u2019re talking, and mirrors your gestures.\n   - His body language is open and engaged when he\u2019s around you.\n\n### 10. **Subtle Hints**\n   - He drops hints about being single or asks questions about your dating life.\n   - He might bring up topics like relationships or compatibility in a joking or casual way.\n\n### What to Do Next:\nIf you\u2019re unsure, trust your instincts. If you like him back, consider giving him subtle signals that you\u2019re open to something more. If you don\u2019t feel the same way, be kind and respectful of his feelings while maintaining the friendship. Sometimes, being direct (if it feels right) can help clarify things for both of you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
